{
  "texts": [
    "However, a discernible gap remains in evaluating the effectiveness of these promises to significantly enhance the quality of automated literature reviews, offering a more scalable and efficient alternative to traditional methods.",
    "Aims and ScopeThis study aims to rigorously evaluate the effectiveness of applying the Mistral LLM, augmented with Retrieval-Augmented Generation, to the task of conducting automatic literature reviews on a collection of 50 scientific papers from the OpenReview platform.",
    "By comparing the outcomes of Mistral LLM's reviews with those conducted by human reviewers, this research seeks to assess the model's proficiency in capturing the essence of scientific literature, its attention to detail, and its overall comparability to human effort.",
    "The scope of this study encompasses the development of a systematic framework for both conducting these reviews and evaluating their quality, setting the groundwork for future research in the automation of literature reviews with advanced LLMs.",
    "Major ContributionsThis study makes three significant contributions to the field of automatic literature reviews using LLMs, specifically focusing on the Mistral LLM enhanced with RAG:1."
  ]
}